19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
20
21 NEW SECTION. SECTION 1. ELIGIBILITY OF LAND FOR VALUATION AS SUSTENANCE USE LAND. (1)
22 CONTIGUOUS PARCELS OF LAND OF more than 20 acres and LESS THAN 640 ACRES UNDER ONE OWNERSHIP THAT ARE
23 ACTIVELY DEVOTED TO SUSTENANCE USE ARE ELIGIBLE FOR VALUATION, ASSESSMENT, AND TAXATION AS AGRICULTURAL
24 LAND IF:
25 (A) THE LAND IS USED PRIMARILY FOR GROWING FRUITS, VEGETABLES, AND GRAINS OR FOR RAISING
26 LIVESTOCK FOR PERSONAL HOUSEHOLD CONSUMPTION OR NONCOMMERCIAL COMMUNITY FOOD SHARING;
27 (B) THE LAND HAS AN OWNER-OCCUPIED RESIDENTIAL DWELLING ON THE PARCEL;
