1 (C) AT LEAST 60% OF THE LAND AREA IS ACTIVELY CULTIVATED FOR FOOD PRODUCTION; AND
2 (D) THE LAND IS NOT USED FOR ANY COMMERCIAL OR INDUSTRIAL PURPOSE.
3 (2) LAND MAY NOT BE VALUED AS SUSTENANCE USE LAND IF MORE THAN $500 OF ANNUAL GROSS INCOME
4 IS DERIVED FROM SURPLUS PRODUCTION.
5 (3) LAND THAT IS DEVOTED TO RESIDENTIAL USE OR THAT IS USED FOR AGRICULTURAL BUILDINGS MUST BE
6 CLASSIFIED AS SUSTENANCE USE LAND, AND THE LAND MUST BE VALUED AS PROVIDED IN 15-7-206.
7 (4) THE OWNER OF THE PROPERTY SHALL SUBMIT A SUSTENANCE USE ATTESTATION ANNUALLY BY MARCH
8 1 ON A FORM PRESCRIBED BY THE DEPARTMENT. THE FORM MUST INCLUDE:
9 (A) A SIGNED STATEMENT OF NONCOMMERCIAL AND NONINDUSTRIAL USE OF THE LAND;
10 (B) AN INVENTORY OF CROPS GROWN AND LIVESTOCK RAISED;
11 (C) FOOD PRESERVATION DOCUMENTATION; AND
12 (D) A STATEMENT THAT THE PROPERTY OWNER ENGAGED IN A MINIMUM OF 100 HOURS PER YEAR OF
13 ACTIVE CULTIVATION OF FOOD FROM THE LAND.
